<a class='reflink' href='../3.dcf/3.1.dpapi.html#theoremperpisnotenough'>3.1.17</a>

<!-- 3.1.17 -->
<div class='toload theorem''>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Theorem 3.1.17</span>
	Suppose that:
	<ol>
		<li>
			$X$ and $Y$ are separable, locally compact Hausdorff spaces;
		</li>
		
		<li>
			For all nonempty $A\in\operatorname{RO}_K(X)$ and $B\in\operatorname{RO}_K(Y)$, $\Sigma_X(A)$ and $\Sigma_Y(B)$ are nonempty;
		</li>
		
		<li>
			$\varphi:\operatorname{RO}_K(X)\to\operatorname{RO}_K(Y)$ is an order isomorphism (with respect to set inclusion).
		</li>
	</ol>
	Then $C_c(X)$ and $C_c(Y)$ are $\perp$-isomorphic.
	</p>
</div>